definition: to stand out from the masses (idiom)
abbr. for 眾議院|众议院[Zhong4 yi4 yuan4], House of Representatives

sentences.english: One of the Murphys' neighbors also noticed 'unusual' traits.
sentences.chinese: 墨菲夫妇的一个邻居也注意到他们与众不同的特点。

sentences.english: Being different, sometimes awkwardly so, comes naturally to Newfoundlanders.
sentences.chinese: 与众不同，有时很别扭，纽芬兰人。

sentences.english: "Before the matches he said that we can start the year loud, " said Kirilenko.
sentences.chinese: “比赛前他说我们要新年与众不同，”基里连科说。

sentences.english: Don't feel embarrassed about being different from others in public.
sentences.chinese: 不要因为你在公共场合的与众不同而发窘。

sentences.english: Fruity-bitter cocktail based on rum, original and different.
sentences.chinese: 朗姆味的水果苦酒鸡尾酒，原创的，与众不同的。

sentences.english: Yes, I know that everyone thinks that his or her projects are different.
sentences.chinese: 我们知道每个人都认为他自己的项目是与众不同的。

sentences.english: Her style of dress is definitely off-beat.
sentences.chinese: 她的服装确实与众不同。

sentences.english: What makes this novel stand out, however, is the nation itself.
sentences.chinese: 使这部小说与众不同的，却是这个国家本身。

sentences.english: Food-gradeessences can add very strange flavours indeed.
sentences.chinese: 加入食物香精的确获得一种与众不同的香味。
沙逊有个与众不同的“处方”。

sentences.english: This post showcases the most unusual and creative advertising campaigns.
sentences.chinese: 这篇帖子陈列了最与众不同和有创意的广告宣传。

sentences.english: I will wear no clothes, which will distinguish me from my fellowmen .
sentences.chinese: 我不会穿衣服的，这样我就会显得与众不同。

sentences.english: Her creations at that time of woman writer in different.
sentences.chinese: 她的创作在当时的女性作家群中与众不同。

sentences.english: Why should we think that the 2012 legends are anydifferent?
sentences.chinese: 那为什么我们要认为2012年的传说与众不同？

sentences.english: Our customers like it because it is so unusual.
sentences.chinese: 我们的顾客喜欢它，因为它是如此与众不同。

sentences.english: This candidate differed from the others.

definition: having a unique or distinctive style
unique and unmatched (idiom); unrivalled/nothing compares with it
lit. to fly one's banner on a solitary tree (idiom); fig. to act as a loner/to stand out/to develop one's own school/to have attitude of one's own
out of the ordinary/unusually (good, talented etc)
to make a show of being original or unconventional (idiom)
to own exclusively/unique to/specific/there is only
to hit on sth new (idiom); to display originality/to adopt an original approach
variant of 別緻|别致[bie2 zhi4]
standing above the common crowd (idiom); outstanding/excellent and unrivaled
out of the ordinary/out of the common run
